comment_regular_data.body:
@bqv I would say no, what would be really required for the use case you describe is a protocol to let UIs negotiate who has reponsability for rendering each UI element.

Theoretically speaking, there is nothing preventing UIs from coming up with such a protocol and implementing it on their own at the moment (in fact I implemented such a protocol in Firenvim 3-4 years ago).

I never knew much about Neovim internals and forgot most of what I knew about UIs though, so I could be wrong :)
